text: Kizray () is a rural locality (a village) in Pervomaysky Selsoviet, Meleuzovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 342 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 20 km from Meleuz, 12 km from Pervomayskaya. == References == Category:Rural localities in Meleuzovsky District
title: Kizray
